counterharm_coi:
Create a cozy Python tool ta sort wir bairns’ storybook picks, lass. We’ll mak a wee helper ta pick oot da tales wir favorit characters an hoo lang dey tak ta read, so aabody can mind whit’s best ta share afore bed. Here’s da snippet ta dae da job: `from sklearn.base import BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin
class BookPicker(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    def __init__(self, columns):
        self.columns = columns
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    def transform(self, X):
        return X[self.columns]`. Aye, dis bit o code lets wis choose only da bits o data wir needin, like story names an readin time. It’s made ta keep wir records neat an easy ta scan, nae bother. Jist pass da column names wis wantan, an da tool’ll dae da rest. A simple way ta mind wir wee readers’ joys, aye?

original_input:
To connect to a MySQL database using PHP, you can use the following code snippet:

```php
<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "username";
$password = "password";
$dbname = "database_name";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}
echo "Connected successfully";

// Close connection
$conn->close();
?>
```

